x
2^{-100x} = (0.5)^{x-4}
0.5=\frac{1}{2}=2^{-1}
2^{100x}=(2^{-1})^{x-4}=2^{4-x}
 -100x\ln\left(2\right) = \left(x - 4\right)\ln\left(0.5\right) = x\ln\left(0.5\right)- 4\ln\left(0.5\right)\,, \quad x = {4\ln\left(0.5\right) \over 100\ln\left(2\right) + \ln\left(0.5\right)} 
\ln\left(0.5\right) = -\ln\left(2\right)
 \color{#ff0000}{\large x} = {-4\ln\left(2\right) \over 100\ln\left(2\right) - \ln\left(2\right)} = \color{#ff0000}{-\,{4 \over 99}} 
